# Responsive & Adaptive Layout

REGO is **phone-first but rotates** — every screen must work in **portrait and
landscape**, across small and large phones, with the user's text-size setting
honoured. Helpers live in `core/utils/responsive.dart`: `AppBreakpoints`,
`context.windowSize`, `context.isLandscape`, `context.textScaler`.

## Never

- Never hardcode a pixel width/height for a layout container (fixed icon/avatar sizes are fine).
- Never assume portrait. The app is **not** orientation-locked — don't add
  `SystemChrome.setPreferredOrientations` unless one specific screen truly requires it.
- Never disable text scaling (no `MediaQuery(textScaler: TextScaler.noScaling)`).
- Never build a non-scrollable screen body — landscape height is short and the keyboard eats most of it.

## Always

- Derive size from `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context)` / `context.windowSize`, or measure with
  `LayoutBuilder`. Use fractions, `Flexible`/`Expanded`/`Wrap` — not fixed boxes.
- Wrap page bodies in `SafeArea` and make them scrollable (`SingleChildScrollView` / `ListView`)
  so they survive landscape + an open keyboard.
- Keep `Scaffold.resizeToAvoidBottomInset: true` (default) on forms; for content pinned above the
  keyboard, account for `MediaQuery.viewInsetsOf(context).bottom`.
- On wider screens, constrain content to `AppBreakpoints.maxContentWidth` and center it — don't
  stretch a form full-bleed across a landscape/tablet width.
- Respect `context.textScaler`; let text grow and reflow. Verify screens at large text scales.

## Orientation (rotation)

- Branch on `context.isLandscape` (or `OrientationBuilder`) when the layout changes shape — e.g. a
  stacked hero-over-form in portrait becomes side-by-side `hero | form` in landscape.
- State survives rotation via Riverpod providers and `State` — don't re-fetch on rebuild. Give list
  items stable `Key`s so scroll position is retained across the rotation.
- Re-check overflow after rotating: a `Column` that fits in portrait often overflows the short
  landscape height — make it scrollable, or switch to a `Row`/`Wrap`.

## Window size classes (Material 3)

| Class | Width | Typical | REGO behaviour |
|-------|-------|---------|----------------|
| `compact` | < 600 | phone portrait | single column |
| `medium` | 600–839 | phone landscape, small tablet | single column, centered, max-width |
| `expanded` | ≥ 840 | tablet | headroom for master/detail later |

## RTL

Combine with `localization.mdc`: use `EdgeInsetsDirectional` and start/end (never left/right) so
responsive layouts still mirror correctly in Arabic.
